com.thinkaurelius.titan.core

Interface TitanElement

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Comparable<TitanElement>, com.tinkerpop.blueprints.Element, com.thinkaurelius.titan.util.datastructures.Removable
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    TitanEdge, TitanKey, TitanLabel, TitanProperty, TitanRelation, TitanType, TitanVertex

    public interface TitanElement
extends com.tinkerpop.blueprints.Element, Comparable<TitanElement>, com.thinkaurelius.titan.util.datastructures.Removable
    TitanElement represents the abstract concept of an entity in the graph and specifies basic methods for interacting with entities. The two basic entities in a graph database are TitanRelation and TitanVertex. Entities have a life cycle state which reflects the current state of the entity with respect to the TitanTransaction in which it occurs. An entity may be in any one of these states and any given time:
    • New: The entity has been created in the current transaction
    • Loaded: The entity has been loaded from disk into the current transaction and has not been modified
    • Modified: The entity has been loaded from disk into the current transaction and has been modified
    • Deleted: The entity has been deleted in the current transaction
    Depending on the concrete type of the entity, an entity may be identifiable, i.e. it has a unique ID which can be retrieved via getId() (use hasId() to determine if a given entity has a unique ID).
    Author:
    Matthias Bröcheler (http://www.matthiasb.com)
    See Also:
    TitanVertex, TitanRelation

    • Method Detail

      • getId

        Object getId()
        Returns a unique identifier for this entity.

        The unique identifier may only be set when the transaction in which entity is created commits. The Graph Configuration Wiki explains how to configure when entity idAuthorities are assigned. Some entities are never assigned a unique identifier if they depend on a parent entity.

        Specified by:
        getId in interface com.tinkerpop.blueprints.Element
        Returns:
        The unique identifier for this entity
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - if the entity does not (yet) have a unique identifier
        See Also:
        hasId()

      • getID

        long getID()
        Unique identifier for this entity. This id can be temporarily assigned and might change. Use getId() for the permanent id.
        Returns:
        Unique long id

      • hasId

        boolean hasId()
        Checks whether this entity has a unique identifier.

        Note that some entities may never be assigned an identifier and others will only be assigned an identifier at the end of a transaction.

        Returns:
        true if this entity has been assigned a unique id, else false
        See Also:
        getID()

      • remove

        void remove()
        Deletes this entity from the graph.

        Removing an entity assumes that the entity does not have any incident TitanRelations. Use Graph.removeEdge(com.tinkerpop.blueprints.Edge) or Graph.removeEdge(com.tinkerpop.blueprints.Edge) to remove an entity unconditionally.

        Specified by:
        remove in interface com.tinkerpop.blueprints.Element
        Specified by:
        remove in interface com.thinkaurelius.titan.util.datastructures.Removable
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - if the entity cannot be deleted or if the user does not have permission to remove the entity

      • getProperty

        <O> O getProperty(TitanKey key)
        Retrieves the value associated with the given key on this vertex and casts it to the specified type. If the key is out-unique, then there can be at most one value and this value is returned (or null). If the key is not out-unique, then a list of all associated values is returned, or an empty list of non exist.

        Parameters:
        key - key
        Returns:
        value or list of values associated with key
